<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><p>Bimetallic Ce/Zr-UiO-66 metal-organic frameworks are promising materials for various catalytic applications, representing, together with other bimetallic MOFs, a new generation of porous materials. However, no direct proof for the presence of both metals in a single cornerstone of UiO-66 MOF was reported so far. Employing element-selective XAS techniques herein we were able to shed light on this matter <ref type="bibr" target="#b0">[1]</ref>. Besides, we were able to demonstrate the possibility to reduce a single Ce ion in the pure Ce-UiO-67 MOF upon the interation with TEMPO [2].</p></div>
			</abstract>
		</profileDesc>
